JIRA currently triggers webhooks on four events: issue created, issue updated, issue deleted, and worklog updated. It would be convenient if JIRA also trigged webhooks on events related to users: for example, "user created", "user added to group", "user removed from group", "user deleted", etc.

For my specific use case, my company has a public-facing JIRA installation with Self Sign Up enabled, and no restrictions on domain. However, we want to automatically place users in JIRA groups based on the domain of the email address they use to sign up. (When employees of the company sign up, they should have more access and permissions than when non-employees sign up.) It would be very helpful to have an "issue created" webhook, so that the webhook handler could inspect the newly-created user via the REST API, and assign that user to the correct group based on the domain of their email address.

